[[Image:St cedds college.png|thumb|right|250px|St. Cedd's College in the online [[Shada]] [http://www.bbc.co.uk/doctorwho/classic/webcasts/shada/ remake] ]]
[[File:Wills Hall, University of Bristol.JPG|thumb|right|250px|[[Wills Hall]] at the [[University of Bristol]] was used as St. Cedds for the [[Dirk Gently (TV series)|2012 television adaptation]].]]
'''St. Cedd's College''' is a [[List of fictional Cambridge colleges|fictional college]], created by [[Douglas Adams]], of [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge University]].
It appears in the ''[[Doctor Who]]'' serial ''[[Shada]]'', and in the novel ''[[Dirk Gently's Holistic Detective Agency]]''.

It is the home of [[Professor Chronotis]], a retired time traveller who appears in Adams' fiction, and—in the fictional universe—was also the college of [[Isaac Newton]] (who attended [[Trinity College, Cambridge|Trinity]]) and [[Samuel Taylor Coleridge]] (who attended [[Jesus College, Cambridge|Jesus]]). It was named after [[Cedd|Saint Cedd]], brother of [[Chad of Mercia|Saint Chad]] (after whom [[St Chad's College, Durham]] is named), whom [[Dirk Gently|Gently]] describes as "one of the duller [[Northumbria]]n saints."

It is based somewhat on Adams's own college, [[St John's College, Cambridge|St John's]]. For ''Shada'', scenes at St. Cedd's were filmed on location at [[Emmanuel College, Cambridge|Emmanuel College]]. In a 2012 episode of the TV adaptation ''[[Dirk Gently (TV series)|Dirk Gently]]'', [[Wills Hall]] at the [[University of Bristol]] was used as St. Cedd's College instead.

{{quote|St Cedd’s College ... owes a little to my memories of St John’s College, Cambridge, although I’ve also borrowed indiscriminately from other colleges as well.  The point is that St Cedd’s College is a completely fictitious assemblage, and no correspondence is intended between any institutions or characters in this book and any real institutions or people, living, dead, or wandering the night in ghostly torment.<ref>[[Dirk Gently's Holistic Detective Agency]]</ref>}}

St. Cedd's College is also mentioned in the [[Torchwood]] online game, made during the show's [[Torchwood (series 2)|second series]]. It is said to be the college attended by Dr. John Winters, a fictional character within the game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newedenbiotech.co.uk/directorsprofiles.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-02-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823042930/http://newedenbiotech.co.uk/directorsprofiles.html |archivedate=2011-08-23 |df= }}</ref>

